  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choosing the Wrong Activity License</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Each license limits what services you can legally offer. If you get a "Marketing Consultant" license but want to do software development, you'll need to amend your license (additional fees). Research permitted activities carefully before applying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Skipping Health Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">In Dubai and Abu Dhabi, health insurance isn't optional—it's legally required. Fines are AED 500/month for non-compliance. Some people try to delay insurance to save money, but this creates problems at visa renewal and can result in significant penalties.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Dubai Living Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Dubai is expensive. If you're earning $4,000/month, most of it goes to rent and living expenses. The tax savings only become significant at higher income levels. Budget carefully—or consider living in Sharjah/Ajman (cheaper) while working in Dubai.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting About Renewal Fees</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The freelancer license is an annual commitment. You'll pay the license fee every year, plus insurance, plus any other costs. Factor this into your long-term planning. Some people are surprised by renewal costs after year one.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Getting Emirates ID Promptly</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Emirates ID is essential for everything—bank accounts, phone contracts, hotel check-ins, even some restaurant deliveries. Apply immediately after your medical test. Delays in getting your Emirates ID cause frustrating complications in daily life.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

